OpenGL provides fast rendering for previews (Fast Draft mode). After Effects can take advantage of GPU (graphics processing unit) on your graphics card for some specific kinds of processing. The GPU features in After Effects are of the following 3 categories:1  GPU-accelerated ray-traced 3D renderer (CUDA on specific graphics cards).penGL, the GPU, and After Effects. OpenGL is a set of standards for high-performance processing of 2D and 3D graphics on the graphics processing unit (GPU) for a wide variety of applications.
